{
  "stem": "8527.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My features were not that abnormal where I-- I don't think so, but I was always afraid that if somebody wants to know if you're Jewish, it's very easy.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Drop your drawers and that's it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So anyway.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And trying to realize-- I'm trying to think who did I feel worse for?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did I feel bad for them because they were dead, or did I feel bad for myself because I was orphaned?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I've never really been able to resolve that, because there's-- there are feelings there of the pain and the suffering that they went through in dying, and also of me being alone.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I've been alone since I was what?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Eight, nine years old.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at my age now, it seems trivial, but all my years, I've never had anybody that said to me I love you or that I care for you.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or-- I never thought about it, because I didn't-- I thought it was-- that was my lot in life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I accepted that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But now, in retrospect, I think about a lot of things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What it's like to grow up, to be knocked around from one orphanage to another orphanage, to have to eat in different families' homes as a beggar, because there was nobody there to take care of you?",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the people didn't have enough food to take care of themselves.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was taking food away from them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so they would send me from one house to another house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that created a tremendous resentment for those people, not just being grateful, just being resentful that I had to go through this.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know whether I'm making myself clear but-- so anyway, that's what started happening after the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
